From ebd0f3453116ec72cd10b2383dd2e35a04c1a24f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 20:04:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Audit pass: remove dead full-table-scan cache method, fix
 stale-closure auto-refresh bug, trim unused fields from resolveFeedRules,
 batch folder cache-busting

- server/db.js, server/db-supabase.js: remove cacheEntries() entirely.
  It had zero remaining callers after the last two commits' fixes, and
  leaving an unbounded full-table-pull method sitting around unused is
  exactly the kind of landmine that caused the 504/timeout bug in the
  first place -- someone (or some future me) reaching for the obvious-
  looking 'get everything' method next time is how this happens again.
- src/main/index.js: this file turned out to have its OWN duplicate copy
  of the same three call sites (startup prune, feed-rules cache-bust,
  clear-all-cache) that server/index.js already had fixed -- missed
  entirely in the last two commits since attention was on
  server/index.js specifically. Since cacheEntries() is now gone from
  both stores, these three spots would have thrown outright if this
  file's createStore() ever resolved to SupabaseStore (it uses the same
  factory as server/index.js, so it's not guaranteed to always be
  JSONStore). Fixed all three the same way: cachePruneExpired /
  cacheDeleteByFeedId / cacheClearAll. Also cleaned up orphaned braces
  left over from the removed for-loop in the feed-rules route.
- server/index.js: resolveFeedRules was computing and merging
  titleBlocklist and inlineBrowser on every feed on every fetch-all call
  -- confirmed against src/core/fetcher.js that neither field is ever
  read server-side (both are client-side-only filters, already handled
  separately in App.jsx). Trimmed to just the three fields fetcher.js
  actually consumes (hideShorts, preferFeedContent, fetchStrategyOrder).
- server/index.js, server/db-supabase.js, server/db.js: folder-level
  settings PATCH was busting cache with one DELETE per feed in the
  folder (Promise.all over N individual round-trips); added
  cacheDeleteByFeedIds for a single batched delete instead.
- src/renderer/App.jsx: the auto-refresh timer closed over feeds_ at
  whatever value it had when the effect last ran ([refreshIntervalMinutes,
  feeds_.length] deps), so adding one feed and removing another between
  ticks (anything that doesn't change the count) would silently refresh
  a stale feed list until the count next changed. Added feedsRef,
  mirroring the existing articlesRef pattern, so the timer always reads
  the current list.
---
 server/db-supabase.js | 28 ++++++++++++++++------------
 server/db.js          | 12 +++++++++---
 server/index.js       | 26 ++++++++++++++++----------
 src/main/index.js     | 23 ++++++++++++++---------
 src/renderer/App.jsx  | 11 ++++++++++-
 5 files changed, 65 insertions(+), 35 deletions(-)

